The _ktila_ noun pattern: The _haktala_ noun pattern is one of the [[hebrew noun patterns]] and produces words such as:
| *Shoresh* | *_Pa’al_ verb* | *_Haktala_ Noun* |
|-|-|-|
| אכל <br> eating | אָכַל<br> _auchal_ <br> he ate | אֲכִילָה <br> _achilau_ <br> an instance of eating |
| הלך<br> eating | הָלַךְ<br> _haulach_ <br> he walked | הֲלִיכָה<br> _halichau_ <br> an instance of walking |
| נפל <br> falling | נָפַל<br> _naufal_ <br> he fell | נְפִילָה <br> _nafila_ <br> an instance of falling |
The _ktila_ pattern is one of the [[noun patterns that come from _pa’al_ verbs]]. More examples of words in the _ktila_ noun pattern [can be found on Pealim](https://www.pealim.com/dict/?pos=noun&nm=qtila).
